    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-15T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-15T09:00:00-05:00" n="179"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d179">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.61331/36: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-15T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 15, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 15—10:08 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1659. Department’s 949, September 13, 9 p.m. Stanley reiterates contents of my
                    1620, September 13, 1 p.m. and points out that it is not that they do not want
                    to buy tobacco from us but that they just have to conserve their exchange for
                    things they need now, not 3 years from now. My own impression is that if they
                    can resume tobacco purchases they will, but at present I see very little
                    hope.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
